dc_title_s: Greene County, Iowa, 1953, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BZP. Form of individual image numbering: BZP-2M-[number], or BZP-3M-[number]. Date of publication inferred from data on individual photographs within the mosaic. Flown by Aero Exploration Company, Tulsa, Oklahoma. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
dc_publisher_s: United States. Department of Agriculture. Production and Marketing Administration
